This paper deals with reinforcement learning, which is a subfield of machine learning. The use of linear function approximation suggests that it belongs to the sub-category of "cs.LG" (Machine Learning). The paper also discusses the adaptation of the Cramer distance, which is a statistical measure, indicating that it could also belong to "cs.AI" (Artificial Intelligence) or "cs.DS" (Data Structures and Algorithms). The use of formal guarantees in the context of policy evaluation suggests that it could belong to "cs.SY" (Systems and Control) as well. Finally, the paper deals with convergence of a distributional algorithm, which is a common topic in "cs.NE" (Neural and Evolutionary Computing).
